- `api/app/_utils/` - Houses utility modules for various functionalities like AWS integration, CMMS (Computerized Maintenance Management System) interactions, distribution utilities, and recursive parent object finding.
- `api/app/core/` - Directory for core business logic and functionalities, potentially including modules like commissioning.
- `api/app/custom_types.py` - Defines custom Pydantic or type hint definitions (e.g., AnnotatedDeep, OptionalListOfInts, OptionalListOfUUIDs) used across the application for data validation and clarity.
- `api/app/dependencies.py` - Defines FastAPI dependency injection functions, commonly used for things like authentication, database session provision, and user data retrieval.
- `api/app/interfaces.py` - Contains interface definitions or abstract base classes that define contracts for other components in the application.
- `api/app/logger.py` - Configures logging for the application, setting up handlers, formatters, and log levels.
- `api/app/main.py` - The main entry point for the FastAPI application. It initializes the FastAPI app, includes routers, and sets up middleware.
- `api/app/schemas/` - Directory containing Pydantic schemas used for request/response validation, serialization, and data structuring (e.g., `calendar.py`).
- `api/app/utils.py` - General utility functions and helper methods that are broadly applicable across the backend application.
- `api/app/v1/` - Contains all API version 1 endpoint modules, organized by resource or functionality (admin, analytics, commissioning, etc.).

### `core/` database models structure:

This directory involves the database structure and its tables and columns.

- `core/_alembic_migrations/` - Historical/archived alembic migrations performed.
- `core/src/core/models.py` - All database models are defined here, including table_name, table_args, columns, etc.
- `core/src/core/database.py` - Manages database connection setup, session management, and engine configuration for SQLAlchemy.

To run an alembic migration, run `source .venv/bin/activate` and then `poe db "[DESCRIPTION]"`

